ANC NEC member Mathole Motshekga has written an open letter on the principle of appealing to the conscience of Jacob Zuma. JOHANNESBURG African National Congress (ANC) NEC member Dr Mathole Motshekga has broken rank and joined the party's chief whip Jackson Mthembu and civil society in calls for President Jacob Zuma to step down.Motshekga has written an open letter where he has supported Secretary General Gwede Mantashe s principle of appealing to the conscience of the president.The ANC Member of Parliament previously formed part of the small NEC task team that coordinated the recalling of the former president Thabo Mbeki in 2008.He says the ruling party cannot accept collective responsibility for the actions of the president and all those implicated in the public protectors State of Capture report.Mathole says the founders and ancestors of the ANC will judge the current leadership harshly if it fails to ask Zuma to do the honourable thing and let his deputy to complete his term. There are people within the ANC like the chief whip Jackson Mthembu, there are 101 stalwarts of the organisation who are saying the same, so it s in the public domain that he must resign. 